//console.log("hello") -> window.console.log("hello")

When the timeout happens the code in it will run ONE time
/* setTimeout(() => {
  alert("HEllo MasteR");
}, 3000);
 */

When the interval happens, the code in it will be run every interval
With an if statement and the clearInterval we can stop the interval


let i = 0;
const timer = setInterval(() => {
  console.log("Hello");
  i++;
  if (i === 5) {
    clearInterval(timer);
  }
}, 1000);
